

                                         Integrating Cucumber BDD


    
  
.......................................... Integrating Cucumber BDD into this Framework ..........................        

    1. Add the dependencies for Cucumber
         - Cucumber-Java 
         - Cucumber-testng
    2. Verify whether the Cucumber Eclipse IDE plugin is installed
    3. Create a package say 'features' under 'src/test/java'
    4. Create a feature file say 'Login.feature' under this package
    5. Create a package say 'stepdefinitions' under 'src/test/java'
    6. Create a Class say 'Login.java' under this package
    7. Auto-generate the Step definitions using TinyGerkhin Chrome Plugin
    8. Move the automation code to respective step definitions methods
    9. Create a runner package 
    10. Create a Runner class under it
         - Extend AbstractTestNGCucumberTests
    11. Generate a testng2.xml file and modify like this
    12. Run the testng2.xml file
    13. Mention this testng2.xml file in maven surefire plugin of pom.xml and run using the Maven command (mvn test)

........................................... "dependencies" for Cucumber ...............................................................................          
             
        <dependency>
            <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
            <artifactId>cucumber-java</artifactId>
            <version>7.15.0</version>
        </dependency>
        
        <dependency>
            <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
            <artifactId>cucumber-testng</artifactId>
            <version>7.15.0</version>
        </dependency>   
              
